short_description: measures a company's current share price in relation to its earnings per share (EPS)
full_description: The annualised gross dividend per share for the last reported period, expressed as a percentage of the latest share price
calculation: P/E Ratio = Market Price per Share / Earnings Per Share
extra: indicating how much investors are willing to pay for each unit of a company's earnings
A high P/E suggests investors expect high future growth
while a low P/E may indicate a stock is undervalued or has lower growth prospects

short_description: The annualised gross dividend per share
full_description: The annualised gross dividend per share for the last reported period, expressed as a percentage of the latest share price
calculation: Div yield (%) = 100 * Gross dividend per share (net dividend *100/90)/latest share price
